cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

This paper is about training Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) with quantized activation functions to improve energy efficiency while maintaining state-of-the-art accuracy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of signal processing tools and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on energy efficiency could also place this paper in cs.SY (Systems and Control) and the use of neural networks for image processing could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
